Core Software Engineer		Flatiron Health		New York City, NY, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Our mission is to serve cancer patients and our customers by dramatically improving treatment and accelerating research. Our team is building a disruptive, oncology-specific software platform that connects cancer centers across the world on a common technology infrastructure to address key healthcare challenges. Today, the Flatiron Health OncologyCloud&amp;trade; platform includes the industry-leading electronic medical record for oncology, a first-of-its-kind analytics tool, patient portal, and integrated billing management. Our goal is to help cancer centers and life science companies leverage real-world oncology data at a scale and clinical depth never before seen, to advance cancer care and accelerate research.<br /> <strong>Our engineering team</strong> <br />The Flatiron Health engineering team builds and runs data processing pipelines, algorithmic and human-operated data curation tools, and customer-facing data analytics and visualization products. We build systems that clean, structure and understand clinical-level patient data as we build the largest, most comprehensive set of oncology data intelligence. We scale pipelines to handle the world's oncology data with creative engineering solutions to open-ended oncology data problems.<br /> <strong>Our data</strong> <br />Our data pipeline takes in full clinical patient records and produces normalized, high-fidelity, queryable data that is ready to be mined for medical and operational insights. We&rsquo;ve built a unified data set that is unparalleled in its depth and accuracy, and which gives our partners the capability to ask questions about data that weren't answerable until now.<br /> <strong>Our culture</strong> <br />We work in a fast-paced, high-information-volume environment with complex domain challenges, which means context is key and there's always more to learn and soak up. We want to know oncology data cold &amp;mdash; better than anyone else in the industry &amp;mdash; and we believe doing so requires building a culture where we all like coming to work each day. In our culture, decisions are transparent and data-driven, and people are empowered to make waves.<br /> <strong>Backend Software Engineer</strong> <br />Are you interested in building elegant and scalable systems to help our customers unleash the power of their data?<br /> As a Backend Software Engineer you will: <ul> <li>Design and implement backend components: services, data stores, infrastructure, instrumentation, and deployment</li> <li>Continuously ship new features for our cloud based infrastructure</li> <li>Write simple, elegant, testable code</li> <li>Drive improvements to our backend infrastructures</li> </ul> About you: <ul> <li>You hold a BS, MS, or PhD in computer science or related field</li> <li>You have strong backend experience with languages like Python, C++ or Java</li> <li>You have a good understanding of online relational databases like Postgresql, MySQL or MSSQL.</li> <li>You are passionate about performance, reliability, and scalability of systems</li> </ul> <strong>Full Stack Software Engineer</strong> <br />Are you interested in using modern web technologies to help our customers unleash the power of their data?<br /> As a Full Stack Software Engineer you will: <ul> <li>Design and implement intuitive web interfaces to make complex data accessible and useful</li> <li>Continuously ship new features for our cloud applications, from the backend to the frontend</li> <li>Write simple, elegant, testable code</li> <li>Drive improvements to our backend and frontend infrastructure</li> </ul> About you: <ul> <li>You hold a BS or MS in computer science or related field</li> <li>You have strong frontend web experience with JS, HTML, and CSS</li> <li>You have strong backend experience with languages like Python, Ruby or Java, and SQL databases</li> <li>You are passionate about empowering users and our mission to improve healthcare through technology</li> </ul> Bonus points if you&amp;hellip; <ul> <li>Contribute to open source projects</li> <li>Have developed apps using modern frontend frameworks like AngularJS / Ember.js</li> <li>Have experience in user experience design or user experience research</li> </ul> <strong>Data Software Engineer</strong> <br />Do you want to synthesize data into knowledge?<br /> As a Data Software Engineer you will: <ul> <li>Write useful and impactful software</li> <li>Design and build our data infrastructure, and use it to develop extensible, robust data pipelines</li> <li>Build tools and infrastructure for easy, accessible and flexible data analysis</li> <li>Iteratively develop, operationalize and monitor machine-assisted and statistical solutions to problems</li> </ul> About you: <ul> <li>You hold a BS, MS, or PhD in computer science or engineering</li> <li>You write clean, well-structured, production-quality code in Python, C++ or Java</li> <li>You have built and deployed large-scale data processing pipelines</li> <li>You seek simple approaches to complex problems</li> <li>You are passionate about our mission to improve healthcare through technology</li> </ul> Bonus points if you&amp;hellip; <ul> <li>Have a strong understanding of statistics</li> <li>Have developed distributed data processing systems against large, heterogeneous data sets</li> <li>Understand experimental design, and can build for collection, measurement and interpretation of results</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Flatiron Health’s mission is to serve cancer patients and our customers by dramatically improving treatment and accelerating research. Our team is building a disruptive, oncology-specific software platform that connects cancer centers across the world on a common technology infrastructure to address key healthcare challenges. <br /><br />Today, the Flatiron Health OncologyCloud™ platform includes the indus